$BTC.X With the bitcoin halving programmed to occur approximately every four years, I had an “aha” moment yesterday. I’m sure this has been discussed before elsewhere, but I realized that the bitcoin reward will soon1 decrease to approximately 1 coin per hour. Currently, there are 6.25 coins rewarded to miners every 10 minutes, or 37.5 every hour. In five halvings or approximately 20 years, the reward will decrease to 1.17 per hour!
